#!/bin/bash
# Pull prebuilt build/runner images from a registry and retag them to the
# local names every script expects — a cold machine skips ~15 min of image
# building. Missing images are skipped with a warning (they'll be built
# locally on demand instead).
#
#   b/pull-build-images [registry-prefix] [tag]
#
# Prefix defaults to $TY_IMG_REGISTRY, tag to 'latest'.
set -euo pipefail

cd "$(dirname "$0")/.."

prefix="${1:-${TY_IMG_REGISTRY:-}}"
tag="${2:-latest}"
if [ -z "$prefix" ]; then
  echo "usage: b/pull-build-images <registry-prefix> [tag]   (or set TY_IMG_REGISTRY)" >&2
  exit 2
fi

images=(
  "ty-builder ty-builder"
  "ty-e2e-runner ty-e2e-runner"
  "debiki/talkyard-nodejs talkyard-nodejs"
  "debiki/talkyard-app-dev talkyard-app-dev"
)

for entry in "${images[@]}"; do
  local_name="${entry% *}"
  remote_base="${entry#* }"
  remote="$prefix/$remote_base:$tag"
  echo "=== pull $remote -> $local_name"
  if docker pull "$remote"; then
    docker tag "$remote" "$local_name"
  else
    echo "    (not available — will be built locally when needed)" >&2
  fi
done
